# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# .dockerignore — files that should NEVER be copied into the Docker image.
#
# Two goals:
#   1. Keep the image small and fast to build.
#   2. Avoid baking in stale or sensitive state (secrets, local runs, old
#      Tkinter UI code that the Streamlit deployment doesn't use).
#
# Note: the host filesystem keeps these files — this only affects what lands
# inside the container. Existing Docker volumes (./Quilgo, ./downloads, etc.)
# are still mounted at runtime and work as before.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# --- Legacy Tkinter desktop UI ---------------------------------------------
# Not imported by streamlit_app.py. `app/__init__.py` and `app/config.py` are
# still copied because Streamlit imports `from app import config`. Only the
# `ui/` sub-package (Tk views) and the Tk entry point are excluded.
app/ui/
main.py

# --- PyInstaller / old desktop build artefacts -----------------------------
build/
dist/
*.spec

# --- Python bytecode and virtualenvs ---------------------------------------
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
.venv/
venv/
env/
.Python

# --- Node / Playwright install output --------------------------------------
# These are installed fresh inside the image via `npm install` + `npx
# playwright install` in the Dockerfile. Copying host copies would just
# bloat the image and risk host-vs-container binary mismatches.
node_modules/
playwright-report/
test-results/

# --- Runtime data that belongs on the HOST, not in the image ---------------
# These are all bind-mounted at runtime via docker-compose.yml, so they
# must not be baked into the image or they'd shadow the mount on first run.
Quilgo/
downloads/
playwright_downloader/
check_output/

# --- Secrets & transient files ---------------------------------------------
# `.env` is written by the GUI at Part 1 launch and deleted at the end.
# `selected_quizzes.json` is likewise transient. Both may contain user
# choices (and .env contains credentials) — never ship them in the image.
.env
.env.*
selected_quizzes.json
gui_config.ini
playwright_live.log

# --- Editor / OS noise -----------------------------------------------------
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Editor temporary save files (VS Code / Claude Code atomic-write leftovers)
*.tmp.*

# --- Git metadata ----------------------------------------------------------
.git/
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# --- Docker & CI config (shouldn't be inside the image) --------------------
.dockerignore
Dockerfile
docker-compose.yml
docker-compose.*.yml

# --- Docs / ad-hoc files ---------------------------------------------------
*.md
!README.md
